OL,6,FMr Lane had joined a public services
OL,7,Fscrutiny committee meeting on 14
OL,8,FOctober and introduced himself,
OL,9,Fsaying: "Councillor Malcolm Lane,
OL,10,Frepresenting Mardy and I am a member
OL,11,Fof this committee, thank you."
OL,13,FHowever, Armand Watts, a Labour
OL,14,Fcouncillor and the committee chairman,
OL,15,Fproceeded to look around at his fellow
OL,16,Fcouncillors in the chamber before
OL,17,Fsaying: "Malcolm, I just have an
OL,18,Fobservation here. Are you driving?"
